### Test Orchestration Pattern

### 1. Create Order via Orchestration - Success Case
POST http://localhost:8081/orchestrate/order
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "customer_id": 1,
  "items": [
    {"product_id": 1, "quantity": 2},
    {"product_id": 2, "quantity": 1}
  ],
  "voucher_code": "SAVE10"
}

### 2. Check Workflow Status
GET http://localhost:8081/orchestrate/{{workflow_id}}

### 3. Create Order via Orchestration - Failure Case
POST http://localhost:8081/orchestrate/order
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "customer_id": 1,
  "items": [
    {"product_id": 999, "quantity": 1}
  ]
}

### 4. Check Failed Workflow Status
GET http://localhost:8081/orchestrate/{{failed_workflow_id}}

### 5. Manual Compensation
POST http://localhost:8081/orchestrate/{{failed_workflow_id}}/compensate

### 6. Create Order with Large Quantity (Stock Failure)
POST http://localhost:8081/orchestrate/order
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "customer_id": 1,
  "items": [
    {"product_id": 1, "quantity": 1000}
  ]
}

### 7. Create Order without Voucher
POST http://localhost:8081/orchestrate/order
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "customer_id": 2,
  "items": [
    {"product_id": 1, "quantity": 1}
  ]
}

### 8. Test Multiple Items Order
POST http://localhost:8081/orchestrate/order
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "customer_id": 3,
  "items": [
    {"product_id": 1, "quantity": 1},
    {"product_id": 2, "quantity": 2},
    {"product_id": 3, "quantity": 1}
  ],
  "voucher_code": "SAVE20"
}